document.title: 2023 Indiana Academic Standards: Grades K-12 Music Ensemble

6698E1C851494BEF98633A9985774B13.description:
Create and share varied, personally-developed musical works (individually or
as an ensemble) that address identified purposes and contexts.

D811B208328349D5A859C0F799C36E14.description:
Accurately arrange an advanced melody of their choice, including an
accompaniment, and notate parts for their ensemble using traditional or electronic
sources.

2B0706086915496699DDCFB2FE6BD076.description:
Use standard and/or nontraditional notation to create songs in a variety of
meters that include accurate chord progressions and melodic/rhythmic phrases.

92DC480F708A452CA6BFF648CD95C808.description:
Create and share personally developed arrangements, sections, and short
compositions (individually or as an ensemble) that address identified purposes.

38F8B03863E5455A9427CE260D961A80.description:
Arrange an intermediate melody and provide an accompaniment that
demonstrates an effective beginning, middle, and ending using traditional or electronic
sources.

0EFAD521058041DFB9AC6D85C50B59C1.description:
Use standard and nontraditional notation to create rhythmic phrases, melodic
phrases, and harmonic sequences that involve chord progressions.

99B988A6BB004BE2B305BD8A0A062316.description:
Create and share personally developed melodies and rhythmic passages
(individually or as an ensemble) that demonstrate understanding of characteristics of
music or texts studied in rehearsal.

B8BBE81BD1BC4F9FA16196044B111216.description:
Arrange a given part song by reassigning voice or instrumentation for each
part using traditional or electronic sources.

30C05C137A884E19872FCF43C6795A0E.description:
Use standard and nontraditional notation to create simple rhythmic phrases,
melodic phrases, and two-chord harmonic musical ideas.

66A9EA37B698402A85EBB116027C3C63.description:
Create and share personally developed melodic and rhythmic ideas or
motives (individually or as an ensemble) that demonstrate understanding of
characteristics of music or texts studied in rehearsal.

79E370D4F5F24A09BE61DABB53099354.description:
Plan and arrange an accompaniment to a provided four measure melody
which outlines a simple chord progression.

4A321C8622A94030B27EF9F3EC041AE7.description:
Create and notate rhythms and melodies (four to eight measures) in simple
and/or compound meters using either traditional or nontraditional notation.

F348D8E445DC4D7F819C48F8A87A4CC3.description:
Create a varied repertoire of music by composing and arranging music with both
traditional and nontraditional notation.

7127A8EA322D4472894BCEF00FF4CFCE.description:
Using traditional music notation, including common diacritical and expressive
markings, students will accurately notate the rhythm, melody, harmonic structure, and
form of three and four chord songs that are aurally perceived and/or audiation in
Western and Non-Western music style.

3BC8A9E63B304AF2A438A0440B94BF6F.description:
Using traditional music notation, including common diacritical and expressive
markings, students will accurately notate rhythmic and melodic motifs and melodies that
are aurally perceived and/or audiation.

0F0A5563F3F34BAF8AB798AE25E6DD38.description:
Use gesture, movement, other visual representations, and both traditional and
nontraditional music notation to represent pitch and rhythm patterns, motifs, and short
melodies that are aurally perceived and/or audiation.

08CD8D87812B49AC9ABFA8D55698192F.description:
Use gesture, movement, and other visual representations to represent pitch
and rhythm patterns, motifs, and short melodies that are aurally perceived and/or
audiation.

5CFB59659DA44C2E96C1D33633F38A1E.description: Create a varied repertoire of music by representing audiated music.

3B59BB2EE5F14BB5B63770064DAF5287.description: Improvise musical ideas for a variety of purposes and contexts.

B035985F5764498196583A658E3AF34E.description:
Share varied, personally developed musical works (individually or as an
ensemble) that address identified purposes and contexts.

3C70D37A9B49418690085F92E1A06B3B.description:
Improvise ideas for arrangements, sections, and short compositions for specific
purposes that reflect the characteristic(s) of music from a variety of cultures studied in rehearsal.

A9DB2FC039BA4D698F77D6845799B8CC.description:
Share personally developed arrangements, sections, and short compositions
(individually or as an ensemble) that address identified purposes.

121E3FD1B6B4406B9E7BFADCC38141EB.description:
Improvise ideas for melodies, rhythmic passages, and arrangements for
specific purposes that reflect the characteristic(s) of music from a variety of historical
periods studied in rehearsal.

12E6BB05114F42E685CD88D1BB94536C.description:
Share personally developed melodies, rhythmic passages, and arrangements
(individually or as an ensemble) that address identified purposes.

3232A1331B3F42628F47D6D86CFB6973.description:
Improvise melodic and rhythmic ideas or motives that reflect the
characteristic(s) of music or text(s) studied in rehearsal.

167282AAB82D4DE293636F19F2D30636.description:
Share personally developed melodic and rhythmic ideas or motives
(individually or as an ensemble) that demonstrate understanding of characteristics of
music or texts studied in rehearsal.

1F05A09F4C6D4324AB663A30C50231AA.description:
Create a varied repertoire of music by improvising melodies, variations, and
accompaniments.

8368ED2E83D441918F006BCC11CD6536.description:
Instrumental: Consistently and accurately play alone or in ensembles historical
and contemporary repertoire from Western and non-Western traditions using traditional
and nontraditional notation.

C624B969E6284205B29F38DD26486F4C.description:
Play musical selections with accurate pitch, articulation, rhythm, and
appropriate tempo, dynamics, and balance in advanced level music and demonstrate
sight reading at an appropriate level.

1F6B9AED4F294479B57392CFBDB3266A.description:
Examine, evaluate, and critique, using music reading skills where appropriate,
how the structure and context impact and inform prepared and improvised
performances.

8628670A5D15409A8DAB0DB618E46CA3.description:
Consistently play and monitor correct posture, characteristic tone quality,
accurate tuning and intonation, good breath support, proper bowing, and/or correct
hand position.

62A0695E6DA84489BAE5C0EC0EC46516.description:
Instrumental: Accurately play alone or in ensembles historical and contemporary
repertoire from Western and non-Western traditions using traditional and nontraditional
notation.

FDB107CBE0D643A19D765EF1D3D722DF.description:
Play musical selections with accurate pitch, articulation, rhythm, and appropriate
tempo, dynamics, and balance in medium-advanced level music and demonstrate sight reading at an appropriate level.

66D105862EC94CD3BC170210B126BC7D.description:
Document and demonstrate, using music reading skills where appropriate, how
compositional devices employed and theory based and structural aspects of musical
works may impact and inform prepared and improvised performances.

534EAAA7AF244CFC9833E30DBDE49D6C.description:
Play and demonstrate correct posture, characteristic tone quality, accurate
tuning and intonation, good breath support, proper bowing, and/or correct hand
position.

4239F34CB9544363A497380B8E467B1D.description:
Instrumental: Play alone or in ensembles, historical and contemporary repertoire
from Western and non-Western traditions.

35533557B08B4331B8EE0A3CFE24623A.description:
Play musical selections with accurate pitch, articulation, rhythm, and appropriate
tempo, dynamics, and balance in moderate level music and demonstrate sight reading
at an appropriate level.

C531681F76284719A2A6799891CD1DAE.description:
Demonstrate, using music reading skills where appropriate, how compositional
devices employed and theory-based and structural aspects of musical works impact
and inform prepared or improvised performances.

927B4C2CBF7B45BBBA1DB53861D6ADEF.description:
Play and identify correct posture, characteristic tone quality, accurate tuning and
intonation, good breath support, proper bowing, and/or correct hand position.

D18362F396254DACB175702095057470.description:
Instrumental: Play literature representing a variety of styles expressively,
utilizing appropriate dynamic contrast, phrasing, and articulation alone or in ensembles,
from a score and from memory.

B879AF5D5F684883AD962C18F94C6484.description:
Play musical selections with accurate pitch, articulation, rhythm, and
appropriate tempo, dynamics, and balance with beginning level music and demonstrate
sight reading at an appropriate level.

4E40B59190CB48E09840123F0714C47D.description:
Demonstrate, using music reading skills where appropriate, how knowledge of
formal aspects in musical works inform prepared or improvised performances.

E1F603A95EF146A6999DBFB5D288BD73.description:
Play and become aware of correct posture, characteristic tone quality, accurate
tuning and intonation, good breath support, proper bowing, and/or correct hand
position.

29BFF00160FA4BEBAE70CA6D12115B58.description:
Perform a varied repertoire of music by playing instruments, alone and with others,
from rote memory, and written notation.

C89DF8E69DD147F285AB1405ABC64CAF.description:
Choral: Consistently and accurately sing alone or in ensembles, accompanied
by an a cappella, historical and contemporary repertoire from Western and
non-Western traditions in a variety of languages, and using traditional and
nontraditional notation.

73C22647B3FD4B228DD7AA9169C508DE.description:
Choral: Demonstrate consistently the concepts of vocal health within warm-ups,
breathing exercises, and appropriate repertoire.

57BCC4DE32034B96A45DF136047D71BC.description:
Choral and Instrumental: Sing expressively with attention to blend, balance,
dynamics, phrasing, and articulation.

D4ABE577B31541E78BE949DB2B455CFB.description:
Choral and Instrumental: Appropriate to the ensemble, students will sing
advanced musical selections, scales, and intervals using note names, solfège,
syllables, or numbers and demonstrate sight reading at an appropriate level.

D9037BEDDB644B0A9E26E2DD9348D51E.description:
Choral and Instrumental: Be able to explain proper vocal technique including
good breath control, pitch, diction (choral only), tone quality, and posture.

393BF7FACF404C648E73A9B41C1F74E7.description:
Choral: Accurately sing alone or in ensembles, accompanied by an a cappella
historical and contemporary repertoire from Western and non-Western traditions in a
variety of languages, and using traditional and nontraditional notation.

DC2B3D7EF60C4D8398CE8068D9BF083F.description:
Choral: Explore the concepts of vocal health and how they affect singing
through warm-ups, breathing exercises, and appropriate repertoire.

2D81EC06EF4E492B9334899DBDB44EF2.description:
Choral and Instrumental: Sing expressively with attention to blend, balance,
dynamics, phrasing, and articulation.

43CC79C5F7834E3F9ABD6E37DC22D4B3.description:
Choral and Instrumental: Appropriate to the ensemble, students will sing
medium advanced musical selections, scales, and intervals using note names, solfège,
syllables, or numbers and demonstrate sight reading at an appropriate level.

8B704554DB794F0E9F415872371C1BCC.description:
Choral and Instrumental: Demonstrate, identify, and apply proper vocal
technique including good breath control, pitch, diction (choral only), tone quality, and
posture.

CD723B529AAB450C8659788ACB7602CB.description:
Choral: Sing alone or in ensembles, historical and contemporary repertoire
accompanied from Western and non-Western traditions and a cappella and with
movement or body percussion when appropriate, to enhance authentic performance.

14FA1742069841A4B76990CFFD9169E4.description:
Choral: Demonstrate, using proper vocal technique and expand vocal range
through warm-ups, breathing exercises, and appropriate repertoire.

C25CFCC1DFA14EBDBCFB5F5CC0B2999D.description:
Choral and Instrumental: Sing expressively with attention to blend, balance,
dynamics, phrasing, and articulation.

6A032766ABB54575986CAA8B19C8BBA4.description:
Choral and Instrumental: Sing intermediate musical selections, scales, and
intervals using note names, solfège, syllables, or numbers and demonstrate sight
reading at an appropriate level.

376AE13BE3004D7EA5F37EEE5463EA8A.description:
Choral and Instrumental: Demonstrate and begin to identify proper vocal
technique including good breath control, pitch, diction (choral only), tone quality, and
posture.

1C3A674B0EED4B8CBC1DFF6920100942.description:
Choral: Sing literature representing a variety of vocal styles expressively,
utilizing appropriate dynamic contrast, phrasing, and articulation alone or in ensembles,
from a score and from memory.

D5356A7984E444AFBB4D18060D076553.description:
Choral: Explore, using proper vocal technique and expand vocal range through
warm-ups, breathing exercises, and appropriate repertoire.

912918BD89774ADCAFD44ECA424255DC.description:
Choral and Instrumental: Begin to sing expressively with attention to blend,
balance, dynamics, phrasing, and articulation.

ADB2E45DF9AF4C9A95877617A41F7ADC.description:
Choral and Instrumental: Appropriate to the ensemble, students will sing
beginning musical selections, scales, and intervals using note names, solfège,
syllables, or numbers and demonstrate sight reading at an appropriate level.

35F8DB90576B48CDA0A18BA724B8B498.description:
Choral and Instrumental: Begin to demonstrate proper vocal technique including
good breath control, pitch, diction (choral only), tone quality, and posture.

47D7D9470FAF417FBF1075BB2155C936.description:
Perform a varied repertoire of music by singing, alone and with others, from rote
memory and written notation.

5F29B020F16445AE949B07EAF58D20C6.description:
Express rhythmic patterns, melodic contour, harmonic progression, and
expressive elements in a variety of meters and tonalities and demonstrate them through
movement, body percussion, and/or conducting.

BE440E2E3B0041BBA6C742B39F96070E.description:
Express rhythmic patterns, melodic contour, and harmonic progression in a
variety of meters and tonalities and demonstrate them through movement, body
percussion, and/or conducting.

1907B67909E84A0D848193722F8F7F15.description:
Express rhythmic patterns in a variety of meters and demonstrate them through
movement, body percussion, and/or conducting.

09A182F500DC4460B03C60B779A4681D.description:
Express differences in musical sounds that are higher or lower, faster or
slower, louder or softer, and demonstrate them through movement, body percussion,
and/or conducting.

52C7A85767FE4C65BA6B49EE7CF72348.description:
Listen and respond to a varied repertoire of music by interpreting and expressing
music through movement.

29979036A08747C0A2510E5694138EAE.description:
Develop and justify evaluations of music, programs of music, and
performances based on criteria, personal decision-making, research, and
understanding of contexts.

B26C371E23234891913F35AD555E8980.description:
Justify interpretations of the expressive intent and meaning of musical works
by comparing and synthesizing varied researched sources, including reference to other art forms

10BD9200C14140F2BFD52C648715A9ED.description:
Listen to ensembles performing appropriate repertoire. Describe and analyze
instrumentation, texture, compositional devices, form, style, and genre.

6C462729089247C196EE622A7D831B1B.description:
Evaluate works and performances based on research as well as personally and
collaboratively developed criteria, including analysis and interpretation of the structure
and context.

57C17A0476C9447E869B43EF67EC2D6D.description:
Explain and support interpretations of the expressive intent and meaning of
musical works citing as evidence the treatment of the elements of music, contexts,
(when appropriate) the setting of the text, and varied researched sources.

2F2C231B40A54C8EA49CFCB6A1081B44.description:
Listen to ensembles performing appropriate repertoire. Identify and describe
instrumentation, texture, compositional devices, form, style, and genre.

C79B02898FC4468E8EEDEDC456D9241C.description:
Recognize and describe works and performances based on personally or
collaboratively developed criteria, including analysis of the structure and context.

A41B6AC608AD4B37A7B64FB29C316F94.description:
Explain interpretations of the expressive intent and meaning of musical works,
citing as evidence the treatment of the elements of music, contexts, (when appropriate)
the setting of the text, and personal research.

39C8951DA57D41F883B111FD4F24774E.description:
Listen to ensembles performing appropriate repertoire. Explore instrumentation,
compositional devices, form, style, and/or genre.

9E6F3EDE7A4247A68C70F2D0DB3171EA.description: Using established criteria, recognize the structure and context of music.

9B7586057DA14419BC6ED59DDBDEE2F4.description:
Explore interpretations of the expressive intent and meaning of musical works,
referring to the elements of music, contexts, and (when appropriate) the setting of the
text.

DD116D89DDAA4A199869F95FDE1CAE5D.description:
Listen to ensembles performing appropriate repertoire. Describe style and
genre, and compositional devices.

3FE91CA79FBA42B799C765BE762B1FFC.description:
Listen and respond to a varied repertoire of music by describing, interpreting,
analyzing, and evaluating music and its elemental components.

F781E9849A5B47709ABFA745CEE39D35.description:
Audiate and perform major/three forms of minor scales, all intervals, advanced
rhythmic and melodic patterns using gesture, traditional, and non-standard music
notation.

58694220A90F4D5B8CCFE744B00BE860.description:
Audiate and speak or sing music with a variety of voicings in multiple clefs,
major and minor keys, and various meters using gesture and/or traditional music
notation.

7858804060524165B7B7AC86E2FBCF5D.description:
Audiate and perform advanced scales, intervals, rhythmic and melodic patterns
using gesture and/or traditional music notation.

FB87BE76995E437194EDA460436CFB0E.description:
Audiate and speak or sing music written in appropriate clefs, major and minor
keys, and simple or compound meter using gesture and/or traditional music notation.

E5CD461471394A84A3A2CC378F092698.description:
Audiate and perform intermediate level scales, intervals, rhythmic and melodic
patterns using gesture and/or traditional music notation.

CC5D55CB604A485C9C733714A5A3829A.description:
Audiate and speak or sing music written in appropriate clefs, major and minor
keys, and simple or compound meter using gesture and/or traditional music notation.

55D9AA3A01464537BA8940B9F34C82A2.description:
Audiate and perform basic scales, intervals, rhythmic and melodic patterns
using gesture and/or traditional music notation.

5B26ACE3F46841DC8F3B2CC0F6FF3422.description:
Audiate and speak or sing music written in the clef appropriate for their own
voice/instrument and in major keys, and simple or compound meter using gesture,
and/or traditional music notation.

6CCB450057514AE88C327274CCCECC9F.description: Listen and respond to a varied repertoire of music by audiating music.

380A179A37B74B2691AE2172122DD404.description:
Participate in an ensemble that demonstrates an understanding and
appreciation of music throughout history, from various cultures and within the local
community.

CD67288320094B31B67FEB1D5167CA16.description:
Consistently recognize and apply appropriate genre and style and understand
composer and historical background information in performed music being studied.

72C0FE1D523245EFAC370C31F0B97AD7.description: Research opportunities for careers in music.

18469127D0844ABFB0251C0199F1AD51.description:
Research the roles of various ensembles throughout history, from various
cultures and within the local community.

3A54E55110D34F7E80CE0ADFF5151FB5.description:
Demonstrate and apply appropriate genre and style and understand historical
background information in performed music being studied.

AE43E6D073EF46B2AC6938C0668F9816.description: Explore opportunities and preparation for careers in music.

604B069079A84826BB3BC0C2BDA94726.description:
Explore the roles of various ensembles throughout history, culture and
opportunities for participation in the community.

672714FBA23B4A25A024F02D2753E1D5.description: Begin to demonstrate appropriate genre and style, while understanding composer, and historical background information in performed music.

2D0F120D15A8436EA6D1C28E77F48A89.description:
Discuss the roles of various ensembles throughout history and discuss
opportunities for participation in their own community.

A267A0CA8CC349F8A4E3F0093AFA59DC.description:
Discuss and explore genre, style, composer, and historical background
information in performed music.

24DAF40A3B3241B98F4BDFF2CC08ABCC.description:
Connect with a varied repertoire of music by exploring the relationships between
music and history and culture.

D4870D4E46264E4D94BEFB88D7A60CCA.description:
Recognize the characteristic elements of other art forms and analyze how
they are combined with performed music.

9FE6BDB4E00D4CBAAEEBB36DB0E17EBB.description:
Demonstrate ways in which the principles and subject matter of various
disciplines outside the arts are interrelated within the performed music.

2073BE051F26425D9A576B0CD590CB90.description:
Compare and describe how the characteristic elements of music and the other
arts are used to depict and/or transform events, scenes, emotions, and/or ideas in
performed music.

5599F42E95D743D3922E5EE8FEE8884B.description:
Explain ways in which the principles and subject matter of various disciplines
outside the arts are interrelated within the performed music.

23757C41B7DF4B51BE8F00C9D7BB2500.description:
Demonstrate and connect how the principles of performed music relate to other
arts.

C87612517F104F4590CA19287F172D75.description:
Explore and demonstrate ways in which performed music connects with math,
English/language arts, social studies, and/or science.

AD87707A23F6439498714D3A4820C75E.description:
Discover, identify, and explore how performed music connects to other arts
and humanities.

42AB0D1FAF5542FFBE16DAD1FF29DD9F.description:
Explore ways in which performed music connects with math,
English/language arts, social studies, and science.

EF4AA7CF727F40D7976908DAB994D1A4.description:
Connect with a varied repertoire of music by exploring the relations between
music, the other arts and disciplines outside the arts.

D2FF4672C15F4BDE9915D2815689FFB7.description:
Consistently demonstrate and apply life skills developed in music studies and
activities such as cooperation, effort, perseverance, and respect that transfer to other
disciplines and contexts.

169D16E54CD4454784A560A68E8977EB.description:
Utilize research and personally developed criteria to justify choices made
when selecting music, citing knowledge of the music, and individual and ensemble
purpose and context.

EF05DCF1549B43F586DF82F8C3CCF5F6.description:
Imagine and predict how interests, knowledge, and skills relate to personal
musical choices.

695ED998BEAA45218CCB7CE88999C8A7.description:
Discuss and debate the nature of music appreciation and justify music's value
to society.

D54027C0B3F34B7E9A94C44D6D4EAB93.description:
Explore and describe the role of music and the arts in developing an empathic
society through music that is performed and/or listened to in daily life.

4563804C5571423696F6C8F7BC3900EB.description:
Explore and evaluate personal benefits of performing and/or listening to music
and how each can enrich one's life.

0C0381576FD3492FA5053BE48DE6ABEA.description:
Identify various uses of music in daily life and describe the characteristics that
make music suitable for a specific use.

EE47E6F42786499892FC75B1310BEEC2.description:
Identify and demonstrate individual preference for music that is performed
and/or listened to in daily life.

B11B3E5BC136413788BB9F0C1F194E8D.description:
Identify and practice life skills developed in music studies and activities such
as cooperation, effort, perseverance, and respect that transfer to other disciplines and
contexts.

DE9406A92773440680FA8F75648A7BCF.description:
Demonstrate and explore how personal interests and skills relate to choices
when performing music.

64C82199CB5A408D8BB3AF9F4C93F976.description:
Connect with a varied repertoire of music by exploring the relationships between
music and personal experience.
